Blurb::
Supply a characteristic value to scale each reponse
Description::
Each entry in
\c primary_scales may be a user-specified nonzero characteristic value
to be used in scaling each response. 

Behavior depends on the value of \c primary_scale_type:
\li <tt>scale_type</tt> - behavior of \c primary_scales
\li <tt>'none'</tt>     - ignored
\li <tt>'value'</tt>    - required
\li <tt>'log'</tt>     - optional

If a single real
value is specified it will apply to each function. 

